introduction: This video discusses the virtual conference that is taking place on February 15th and 22nd, featuring keynotes from experts in the field of artificial intelligence, product management, and engineering. The conference will cover topics such as AI product ownership, engineering tracks, and hands-on workshops. The hosts also mention their personal experiences and how the conference has impacted their lives.

sections.title: Section 1: Virtual Conference Overview
content: The virtual conference is taking place on February 15th and 22nd.
It features keynotes from experts in AI, product management, and engineering.
The conference covers topics such as AI product ownership, engineering tracks, and hands-on workshops.
The hosts also mention their personal experiences and how the conference has impacted their lives.

sections.title: Section 2: AI Product Ownership Track
content: The AI product ownership track features experts discussing the role of product owners in the AI industry.
They discuss the challenges and opportunities faced by product owners in the AI field.
The speakers also share their experiences and insights on how to succeed as a product owner in AI.
The session is designed to provide valuable information and insights for product owners looking to work with AI.

sections.title: Section 3: Engineering Tracks
content: The engineering tracks feature experts discussing the latest developments and trends in the AI industry.
They cover topics such as deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision.
The speakers also share their experiences and insights on how to apply these technologies in real-world scenarios.
The sessions are designed to provide valuable information and insights for engineers and developers working with AI.

sections.title: Section 4: Hands-on Workshops
content: The hands-on workshops feature experts leading interactive sessions where attendees can learn by doing.
They cover topics such as data preprocessing, model training, and deployment.
The workshops are designed to provide practical skills and knowledge that attendees can apply in their own projects.
The sessions are designed to be engaging and interactive, allowing attendees to learn from the experts and apply the concepts they learn.

sections.title: Section 5: Personal Experiences
content: The hosts share their personal experiences and how the conference has impacted their lives.
They discuss the challenges and opportunities they faced while working in the AI industry.
The speakers also share their experiences and insights on how to succeed in the AI field.
The session is designed to provide valuable information and inspiration for those looking to work in the AI industry.
